---
description: Guidelines for creating git commit messages for BetAgent.
alwaysApply: false
---

## Format

1. Ticket prefix plus imperative subject: `TICKET-NUMBER: Short descriptive title`
2. Blank line separating title from bullets.
3. Bulleted narrative with `- ` markers, written in present tense, active voice.

## Title rules

- Keep subject between 50-72 ASCII characters excluding the tracker prefix portion.
- Use imperative mood describing the headline change bucket.

## Body rules

- Each bullet summarizes one coherent unit of change; cite modules or filenames when ambiguity exists.
- Group related deltas; omit mechanical noise (“formatting leftovers”, whitespace-only churn).
- If no tracker slug exists yet, fall back prefix `pref` or migrate to plain Conventional Commits (`feat(scope): ...`). Confirm with stakeholders before rewriting history.

```text
BET-101: Harden BullMQ enqueue idempotency

- Add deterministic job identifiers for match analysis backlog replays.
- Document retry caps inside `MATCH_ANALYSIS_QUEUE` producer.
- Extend worker metrics to differentiate duplicate suppressions versus failures.
```
